 only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__defineSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__defineSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupGetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupGetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/__lookupSetter__\"><code>Object.prototype.__lookupSetter__()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/hasOwnProperty\"><code>Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty()</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/isPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/propertyIsEnumerable\"><code>Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/setPrototypeOf\"><code>Object.setPrototypeOf()</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toLocaleString\"><code>Object.prototype.toLocaleString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>Object.prototype.toString()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/pl/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/valueOf\"><code>Object.prototype.valueOf()</code></a></li></ol></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect1\"></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"summary","title":"Podsumowanie","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Funkcja<strong style=\"font-weight: bold;\"> </strong><code><strong>Math.sign() </strong></code>zwraca znak liczby. Wynik wskazuje czy liczba przekazana jako argument jest dodatnia, ujemna lub czy jest zerem.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Składnia","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"syntaxbox notranslate\"><code>Math.sign(<em>x</em>)</code></pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parametry","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"x\"><code>x</code></dt>\n <dd>Liczba, której znak ma zostać określony.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"description","title":"Opis","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Metoda <code>sign</code> powinna być zawsze używana jako <code>Math.sign()</code>, ponieważ&nbsp;jest metodą statyczną w obiekcie <code>Math</code>. (Nie jako metoda stworzonego obiektu&nbsp; (<code>Math</code> nie jest konstruktorem)).</p>\n\n<p>Funkcja ma pięć wartości wynikowych <code>1, -1, 0, -0, NaN,</code> które reprezentują odpowiednio: \"liczbę dodatnią\",&nbsp;\"liczbę ujemną\",&nbsp;\"zero \"dodatnie\"\",&nbsp;<span style=\"line-height: 1.572;\">&nbsp;\"zero \"ujemne\"\" </span><span style=\"line-height: 1.572;\">oraz NaN (parametr nie jest liczbą).</span></p>\n\n<p>Argument funkcji jest domyślnie konwertowany do <code>number</code>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Przykłady","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example_using_math.log","title":"Przykład: Użycie <code>Math.sign</code>","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush:js notranslate\"><code>Math<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">sign</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>     <span class=\"token comment\">//  1</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">sign</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>    <span class=\"token comment\">// -1</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">sign</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"-3\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">// -1</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">sign</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>     <span class=\"token comment\">//  0</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">sign</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>    <span class=\"token comment\">// -0</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">sign</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">NaN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>   <span class=\"token comment\">// NaN</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">sign</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"foo\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// NaN</span>\nMath<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">sign</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>      <span class=\"token comment\">// NaN</span>\n</code></pre></div>","titleAsText":"Przykład: Użycie Math.sign"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"specyfikacje","title":"Specyfikacje","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Specyfikacja</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Komentarz</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/6.0/#sec-math.sign\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">ECMAScript 2015 (6th Edition, ECMA-262)<br><small lang=\"pl\">The definition of 'Math.sign' in that specification.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-standard\">Standard</span></td>\n   <td>Initial definition.</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"tabela_zgodności_przeglądarek","title":"Tabela zgodności przeglądarek","isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect2\"><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/mdn/browser-compat-data\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">We're converting our compatibility data into a machine-readable JSON format</a></strong>.\n            This compatibility table still uses the old format,\n            because we haven't yet converted the data it contains.\n            <strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Structures/Compatibility_tables\" class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\">Find out how you can help! (en-US)</a></strong></div>\n\n<div class=\"htab\" id=\"sect3\">\n    <a id=\"AutoCompatibilityTable\" name=\"AutoCompatibilityTable\"></a>\n    <ul>\n        <li class=\"selected\"><a href=\"#compat-desktop\">Pulpit</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"#compat-mobile\">Mobile</a></li>\n    </ul>\n</div><p></p>\n\n<div id=\"compat-desktop\">\n<table class=\"compat-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th>Feature</th>\n   <th>Chrome</th>\n   <t